lead_paragraph: The Foreign News, which will be found in our columns this morning, is interesting. There seems to be confirmation of the rumered intervention of ENGLAND and FRANCE in regard to Cuba. Each of those Governments was about to address a note to that of the United States upon the subject. The Spanish press are clamorous for calling the American Government to an account for the insult offered to the Spanish Consul at New-Orleans.
